notes: Wyndham Clark won the Wells Fargo Championship by four strokes over Xander Schauffele, earning his first PGA TOUR victory in his 134th start at the age of 29 years, 4 months, 28 days. Clark became the sixth player to earn his first PGA TOUR victory at the Wells Fargo Championship and eighth first-time winner on TOUR during the 2022-23 season.
With a 72-hole total of 265, Clark became the first player in tournament history with a score of 265 or better.
Schauffele finished runner-up for the 11th time in 152 starts.
Three-time champion Rory McIlroy (T47) failed to finish in the top 10 for just the third time in 12 starts at the Wells Fargo Championship (MC/2011, T16/2018, T47/2023).
